There is a language issue here. I'm marking many of these as irrelevant because the wording is "and since." The use of "and" implies that the reason and the first statement msut agree with each other, even if the conclusion does not. I would be able to choose a more relevant reason from the given choice if the given statement read "but since" when the reason and statement are in opposition to each other. Since I don't know your intent, I don't know if this feedback is useful or relevant.
